<font color="#FF0000">MY BEING HUMAN</font><br>
<tt>Fri Aug  1  3:36:53 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Arthur:<br><br>
Once there was a young warrior who was very troubled.  He went to Tunkasila, a grandfather and stated his problem:<br><br>
&quot;Grandfather,&quot; he said, sadly, &quot;I feel as if there are two big, true dogs fighting inside of me.  One is Ta Sunke Manitou Hasapa, a great black wolf who cries out that I am weak, foolish, and worthless.  The other is Ta Sunke Manitou Ska, a fierce white wolf who cries out that I am strong, wise, and of great value to my people.  I am torn, Grandfather, because they fight viciously inside of me.  I am frightened, Grandfather, because I do not know which one will win!&quot;<br>
Out of deep respect, the young man would not look upon the Grandfather.  Tormented, he waited for the Old Man's wisdom.<br>
Finally, Tunkasila smiled and spoke softly, &quot;I know which true dog will win!&quot;  He paused for the young warrior to ponder.  &quot;The wolf that you feed the most will win!&quot; he said.<br>
When you introspect, my brother, look for goodness in yourself... and you will feed the White Wolf.<br><br>
Humming Eagle<br>

